import React from 'react'
import { Header, Icon, Image, Menu, Segment, Sidebar, Button } from 'semantic-ui-react'



const SidebarExampleSidebar = (visible) => {
  function handleClick(visible) {
    visible = !visible
  }

  return (
    <Sidebar.Pushable as={Segment}>
      <Sidebar
        as={Menu}
        animation='overlay'
        icon='labeled'
        inverted
        onHide={() => handleClick(visible)}
        vertical
        visible={visible}
        width='thin'
      >
        <Menu.Item as='a'>
          <Icon name='home' />
          Home
        </Menu.Item>
        <Menu.Item as='a'>
          <Icon name='gamepad' />
          Games
        </Menu.Item>
        <Menu.Item as='a'>
          <Icon name='camera' />
          Channels
        </Menu.Item>
      </Sidebar>

      <Sidebar.Pusher>
        <Segment basic>
          <Header as='h3'>Application Content</Header>
          <Button>Click Me</Button>
        </Segment>
      </Sidebar.Pusher>
    </Sidebar.Pushable>
  )
}

export default SidebarExampleSidebar
